Benchmark for modeling thermal structure of subduction zones
(van Keken et al., Physics of the Earth and Planetary Interiors, 171, 187-197, 2008; 
 https://doi.org/10.1016/j.pepi.2008.04.015)

UM: Peter van Keken, University of Michigan
PGC: Claire Currie, Jiangheng He, Kelin Wang, Pacific Geoscience Centre
PU: Scott King, Purdue University
WHOI: Mark Behn, Woods Hole Oceanographic Institution
Brown: Amandine Cangioncle, Marc Parmentier, Brown University
LDEO: Richard Katz, Marc Spiegelman, Columbia University
NTU: Shu-Chuan Lin, National Taiwan University

cases
1a: isoviscous wedge rheology, heat equation only using Batchelor solution
1b: isoviscous, Stokes solution with Batchelor solution b.c.
1c: isoviscous, Stokes with open b.c.
2a: temperature-dependent rheology 
2b: temperature- and stress-dependent rheology

quantities:
T60: spot temperature at slab surface at 60 km depth
L2 : L2 norm of temperature in select points along slab surface
L2w: L2 norm of temperature in select points in mantle wedge
